title.narrative: Strengthening Health Outcomes through the Private Sector Plus (SHOPS+)

description.narrative: (Nigeria): The SHOPS+ activity partners with clinic-based providers to improve the availability, accessibility, acceptability, and quality of family planning services. Activities will increase access to high quality family planning services in focus states. SHOPS+ will train both private and public sector providers in the provision of family planning services with a focus on using long-acting reversible contraceptives (LARCs). Provider training will be complemented by community mobilization efforts to increase uptake of services, increasing availability of LARCs and ensuring high quality medium-and short-term methods are also available. A robust supervision approach will ensure high quality counseling and services.
